content.description: An unusual opportunity to exit a bomb-bay chimney via an offwidth.
content.protection: A really big cam, some medium nuts, and a couple of hand-sized cams.  This is your opportunity to use that #5 or #6 camalot!
content.location: Where Vulture Overlook offers the tallest expanse of rock, find the alcove with the big roof.  A hand crack goes up the roof to the right (Gram Cracker), and a small bomb-bay chimney marks it on the left.  Stay left.

content.protection: Medium nuts, finger to fist-sized cams.
content.location: On the left, in the first alcove.

content.description: Three boulder problems separated by two resting horizontals. The following words describe this climb: "Bouldery", "Shouldery", "Body Tension", "Technical" and "Intricate".
content.protection: TR or good gear in the horizontals
content.location: This route is a tall face to the right of "Missing Piece".

content.description: A couple of cool jams with excellent pro.
content.location: Right of "The V" is a crack starting on the right side of the overhang. Pull the overhang on excellent jams and then trend left to finish on the top crack of "The V".

content.description: Hand crack through a small roof.  Add the steep face at the top for extra fun.
content.protection:
None for the first 15-20 feet.  Do a few thin moves over a bad landing to start, then easier climbing to the roof where you have good gear.  Or traverse in from "The V", and deal with rope drag. 

  Actually, this is probably most fun as a top-rope.
content.location: Start on the outside corner to the left of "The V."  Climb to the obvious handcrack, and use it.  At the top, climber's choice.

content.description: Climb face between Missing Piece and Magic Mushroom.

Two laser cut cracks in a gently overhanging prow of rock.  One is finger size, the other is a hand crack.  Which one you gonna choose? 

  What you hoped "Via Apia" would be. 

  Not to be confused with "Double Jeopardy" near the Great Chimney.
content.location: Just right of the first alcove, as you walk into Vulture's Overlook from the boulder field.

pathTokens: East Bluff 03 - West of the Quarry

content.description: A quiet crag in the woods, yet easy to find.  Great views across the quarry and Roznos Meadow to the Wisconsin River.  Among the notable climbs here are "Magic Mushroom" (5.12b/c), "Double Jeopardy" (5.9), and "The V" (5.10 offwidth).
